    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-12-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-12-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="12"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d12">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">845C.00/12–1146: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-12-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 16, 1946—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1185. Rangoon advises Burma Govt requesting London grant freedom in conduct
                    external relations and support Burmese admission UN. If London decision
                    favorable Burma wishes establish legations Washington, Delhi, Nanking,
                    Manila.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> does not believe exchange fully accredited
                    ministers advisable until Burmese political situation more clarified. Should
                    Brit and Burma Govts approach us this regard now we would suggest preference for
                    exchange commissioners similar arrangements made with India 1941.</p>
                <p>Foregoing for your information and discreet use. Keep <gloss target="#t_Dept1"
                        >Dept</gloss> informed whether Govt to which you are accredited contemplates
                    early exchange representatives with Burma.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking, New Delhi, and Manila.<note n="28" xml:id="d12fn1">As telegrams
                        1185, 929, and 853, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Repeated London and Rangoon<note n="29" xml:id="d12fn2">As telegrams 8181 and
                        306, respectively.</note> for information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
